University, and died at home, surrounded by his family, at the ripe old age of 80.

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:05.870
Toussaint L’Ouverture was born on a slave plantation in Saint-Domingue, in modern-day Haiti, and

00:02:05.880 --> 00:02:14.200
died at the age of 59 in chains in a freezing French prison, just months after Wordsworth’s poem.

00:02:15.350 --> 00:02:20.500
The fact that this Romantic English poet dedicated a poem to him

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:25.064
gives you some idea of the global impact of Toussaint L’Ouverture.

00:02:26.399 --> 00:02:32.049
And we can see this poignantly in the last few verses, as Wordsworth

00:02:32.060 --> 00:02:36.700
wrote about how L’Ouverture would be remembered by generations to come.

